==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Minish
<hw>Min"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>menusen</ets>, F. <ets>menuiser</ets> to make small, cut small, fr.
(assumed) LL. <ets>minutiare</ets>, for <ets>minutare</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>minutus</ets> small. See <er>Minute</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Diminish</er>, <er>Minge</er>.]</ety> <def>To diminish; to
lessen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The living of poor men thereby <qex>minished</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minishment</ent>⟦br⟧
